info.name: TEAM-6-PURPLE(Testers)
info.description:
This API provides various travel-related services such as itinerary planning, hotel booking, local attractions, and travel advisory updates. Below are the details for interacting with the API.

## Getting Started

To have access to our APIs is easy.

1. Create a User account using our `Register User` endpoint.
    
2. Login with the registered user's credentials to receive a bearer token to access other endpoints.
    

---

# Authentication

Authentication to the Team6Purple API service is performed with the Bearer Token. Every endpoint apart from the Authentication endpoints requires authentication, so you will need to add the following header to each request:

`Authorization: Bearer`

`base_url: https://team-6-purple.onrender.com`

# Data Types

All of the API responses returned are in JSON format, with these data types defined below:

| Type | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `string` | A UTF-8 encoded string |
| `number` | An integer |
| `datetime` | An ISO8601 encoded DateTime. All datetimes are returned in UTC with offset +00:00 |

# Data Length

| Type | Description | Length |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Text fields | `string` | max-length 255 characters |
| Names | `string` | max-length 100 characters |
| Passwords | `string` | at least 8 characters |

---

# Response

| Field | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| data/user/itinerary | `object` | The actual data items you have requested |
| message | `string` | A message that lets you know the outcome of the endpoint |

---

# Errors

Errors are expressed as a combination of HTTP status codes and an accompanying JSON body providing required detail where possible. You should be able to rely on the HTTP status code alone to determine the cause of the problem.

## Error Response Fields

| Field | Type |
| --- | --- |
| message | `string` A human-readable message as to the specifics of the problem. For example, it may contain a detail description of what caused the problem |
| status number | The HTTP status code used in the response |
| error_code | `number` |

---

request.description:
### API Request Description

This POST request is used to register a new user. The request should include the user's first name, last name, email, and password in the request body.

#### Request Body

- `firstName` (string): The first name of the user.
    
- `lastName` (string): The last name of the user.
    
- `email` (string): The email address of the user.
    
- `password` (string): The password for the user's account.
    

### Response

The response to this request will have a status code of 201 and a JSON content type. It will include a message and user details in the following format:

``` json
{
    "message": "User created",
    "user": {
        "id": 0,
        "email": "user's email",
        "password": "user's password(hashed)",
        "firstName": "user's first name",
        "lastName": "user's last name",
        "updatedAt": "timestamp of last update",
        "createdAt": "timestamp of creation"
    }
}

 ```

request.description:
The endpoint `/api/v1/users/login` is a POST request used for user login. It expects a JSON payload in the request body containing the user's email and password.

### Request Body

- `email` (string, required): The email of the user.
    
- `password` (string, required): The password of the user.
    

### Response

The response to this request is a JSON object with the following properties:

- `message` (string): A message related to the login process.
    
- `user` (object): An object containing user details with the following properties:
    
    - `id` (number): The unique identifier of the user.
        
    - `email` (string): The email of the user.
        
    - `password` (string): The password of the user.
        
    - `firstName` (string): The first name of the user.
        
    - `lastName` (string): The last name of the user.
        
    - `createdAt` (string): The timestamp of user creation.
        
    - `updatedAt` (string): The timestamp of user details update.
        
- `token` (string): A token associated with the user's login session.
    

### Response

The response to this request will have a status code of 201 and a JSON content type. It will include a message and user details in the following format:

``` json
{
    "message": "User created",
    "user": {
        "id": 0,
        "email": "user's email",
        "password": "user's password(hashed)",
        "firstName": "user's first name",
        "lastName": "user's last name",
        "updatedAt": "timestamp of last update",
        "createdAt": "timestamp of creation"
    }
    "token": "Bearer Token"
}

 ```

request.description:
# API Request: User Logout

This API endpoint is used to log out a user from the system.

### Response

The response of this request is a JSON object with the following properties:

- `status` (string): The status of the logout operation.
    
- `message` (string): A message indicating the result of the logout operation.
    

Example Response:

``` json
{
    "status": "success",
    "message": "User logged out successfully."
}

 ```

request.description:
# Hotel Location Search

This endpoint retrieves a list of hotels based on the specified location.

## Request

### Request URL

`GET /api/v1/hotels/search-location/:place`

### Request Parameters

- `place` (path): The location for which hotels are being searched.
    

## Response

### Response Body

The response will be in JSON format and will include the following fields:

- `message` (string, optional): A message related to the response.
    
- `data` (array): An array of hotel location search results, each containing the following fields:
    
    - `title` (string): The title of the hotel location.
        
    - `geoId` (integer): The geographical ID of the location.
        
    - `documentId` (string): The document ID associated with the location.
        
    - `trackingItems` (string): Tracking items related to the location.
        
    - `secondaryText` (string): Additional text related to the location.
        

### Example Response

``` json
{
    "message": "",
    "data": [
        {
            "title": "",
            "geoId": 0,
            "documentId": "",
            "trackingItems": "",
            "secondaryText": ""
        }
    ]
}

 ```

request.description:
This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve the list of bookings associated with the user. The request does not require any specific parameters in the request body.

### Request Body

This request does not require a request body.

### Response

Upon a successful execution, the response will have a status code of 200 and a JSON object in the following format:

``` json
{
    "message": "",
    "data": [
        {
            "id": 0,
            "userId": 0,
            "geoId": "",
            "locationId": "",
            "checkIn": "",
            "checkOut": "",
            "adults": 0,
            "rooms": 0,
            "price": "",
            "photos": [""],
            "status": "",
            "createdAt": "",
            "updatedAt": ""
        }
    ]
}

 ```

The `data` array contains the details of the user's bookings, including the booking ID, user ID, location details, check-in and check-out dates, number of adults and rooms, price, photos, status, and creation/update timestamps.
